  "texts": [
    "92 There are also large and more specific government funding efforts for AI-enabled protein engineering such as the US NSF's $40m Use-Inspired Acceleration of Protein Design (USPRD) initiative.",
    "93 There are also strong signals of increased VC funding specifically for AI-enabled protein engineering.",
    "Recent examples include EvolutionaryScale, which raised $142m, 94 and China's Xtalpi, which raised $126.7m from an IPO in Hong Kong, 95 as well as Cradle ($73m), 96 Latent Labs ($50m) 97 and Profluent ($35m). 98",
    "Have there been interventions to increase growth or development of these tools, such as commercialization or scaling up of labs?",
    "3 Yes, there are major interventions which are likely to substantially increase growth or tool development."
  ]
}